  "summary": "At Litcham Manor, a famous British estate owned by the eccentric Hubert Litcham Rock, guests gather for a ceremonial dinner. The household follows a strict tradition where dinner begins precisely after a second bell rings, and latecomers are barred from the manor. Joan Ashby, Harry Dahlhausen, Hubert's secretary Jeffrey Keene, and Hubert's adopted daughter Diana Clifes all express surprise when the ceremony is delayed by ten minutes, noting that Hubert is typically a punctual man.\n\nWhen the butler, Digby, finally sounds the gong to announce dinner, the guests realize that Hubert is missing. Instead of the master of the house, Hercule Poirot enters the room, explaining that his train was delayed by an accident. As the guests, including the muddled Mrs. Litcham Rock, discuss the anomaly, Digby reports that Hubert had gone to his study at 7:52 PM.\n\nThe situation becomes tense when Digby returns to announce that Hubert's study door is locked. Taking charge of the group, Poirot leads the guests to the study. After knocking with increasing force and receiving no response, Poirot examines the keyhole and commands the gentlemen to break down the door immediately.",
